---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import tamaPortrait from '../assets/images/tama-portrait.jpg';
import MagneticButton from '../components/MagneticButton.astro';

const philosophy = [
  {
    title: 'Honesty Over Noise',
    description: 'Advocacy begins with honesty. Communication begins with courage. The truth doesn\'t always make friends \u2014 sometimes it makes waves. We believe meaningful PR starts by saying what needs to be said, clearly and responsibly.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Sustainability with Substance',
    description: 'Sustainability isn\'t a headline \u2014 it\'s a mindset. We tell stories that align purpose with practice, building trust that lasts longer than campaigns.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Stories that Serve',
    description: 'Real PR connects meaningfully. Every message we craft considers people, communities, and long-term impact \u2014 not just visibility or metrics.',
  },
];

const pillars = [
  { number: '01', title: 'Personal Branding & Voice', tagline: 'The foundation where all communication begins.', subtitle: 'Because a voice that knows itself is never forgotten.' },
  { number: '02', title: 'Communication & PR Education', tagline: 'Empowering through knowledge.', subtitle: 'Because understanding how communication works is the first step to using it well.' },
  { number: '03', title: 'Advocacy & Ethical Storytelling', tagline: 'The purpose that fuels our work.', subtitle: 'Because some stories need more than amplification\u2014they need care.' },
  { number: '04', title: 'Corporate & Professional Communication', tagline: 'Building trust at an organizational level.', subtitle: 'Because what happens inside shapes what the world hears.' },
  { number: '05', title: 'Lifestyle, Culture & Human Connection', tagline: 'The human layer of storytelling.', subtitle: 'Because all communication starts with understanding people.' },
];
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Where powerful communication begins with truth. Learn about Tama PR.">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="pt-32 pb-16 bg-warm-white">
    <div class="max-w-[1200px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-16">
      <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[2.5px] uppercase text-terracotta mb-5 reveal">About Tama PR</p>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-[36px] md:text-[42px] lg:text-[56px] text-navy leading-[1.1] max-w-[700px] reveal">
        Where powerful communication begins with truth.
      </h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Who We Are -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-warm-white">
    <div class="max-w-[800px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-16">
      <div class="reveal">
        <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[2px] uppercase text-terracotta mb-5">Who We Are</p>
        <div class="space-y-5 text-[16px] leading-[1.85] text-text-muted">
          <p>
            Tama PR is built on connection&mdash;not just messaging. We believe communication carries responsibility, not just reach.
          </p>
          <p>
            We operate at the intersection of clarity, empathy, and advocacy&mdash;prioritizing understanding before visibility, and intention before performance. Every engagement begins by listening: to the people behind the brand, the values they carry, and the real-world impact their voice creates.
          </p>
          <p>
            This is not transactional PR. It is thoughtful, ethical communication designed to build trust, protect narratives, and strengthen relationships&mdash;especially where communities, livelihoods, or sensitive stories are involved.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Three-line tagline -->
      <div class="mt-10 bg-cream rounded-xl p-8 border-l-3 border-terracotta reveal">
        <div class="space-y-1 font-serif text-[18px] text-navy leading-relaxed">
          <p>Authenticity guides the work.</p>
          <p>Advocacy shapes the approach.</p>
          <p>Truth remains the goal.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Story Behind Tama PR -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-cream">
    <div class="max-w-[800px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-16">
      <div class="reveal">
        <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[2px] uppercase text-terracotta mb-5">Our Origin</p>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-[28px] md:text-[32px] text-navy mb-6">The story behind Tama PR.</h2>
        <div class="space-y-5 text-[16px] leading-[1.85] text-text-muted">
          <p>
            I've always been drawn to how people speak &mdash; and what they leave unsaid.
          </p>
          <p>
            Long before PR became a profession for me, storytelling was how I made sense of the world. I listened closely. I noticed tone, pauses, intention. I paid attention to how words could soften a moment, or harden it. How they could create closeness &mdash; or distance.
          </p>
          <p>
            As I moved through different spaces and industries, I began to see just how much power communication holds. I saw how stories could open doors, build trust, and give people a sense of belonging. But I also saw the other side &mdash; how easily stories could be rushed, simplified, or handled without care.
          </p>
          <p>
            Over time, what disturbed me wasn't the lack of storytelling, but the lack of responsibility around it. Visibility was often prioritized over dignity. Performance over truth. People were reduced to talking points, communities to campaigns, and lived experiences to content.
          </p>
          <p>
            That tension stayed with me.
          </p>
          <p>
            Especially in spaces involving livelihoods, in vulnerability, or identity, I felt a quiet discomfort with how easily narratives could be shaped without consent, context, or care. I began asking myself harder questions &mdash; not just what story is being told, but who is telling it, who benefits, and who carries the consequences.
          </p>
          <p>
            At some point, I realized I didn't want to just participate in communication as it was. I wanted to work differently. Slower. More intentionally. With curiosity instead of extraction. With listening before speaking.
          </p>
          <p class="font-serif text-navy text-[17px]">
            Tama PR grew from that decision.
          </p>
          <p>
            It exists because I believe voice carries responsibility. That behind every brand, every organization, every campaign, there are real people &mdash; with histories, values, and dignity &mdash; who deserve to be represented truthfully and thoughtfully.
          </p>
          <p>
            This work is personal to me. It's shaped by observation, by listening, and by choosing to honor nuance in a world that often rewards noise. I believe stories should not only be effective, but ethical. Not only compelling, but considerate.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Closing statement -->
        <div class="mt-8 space-y-1 font-serif text-[17px] text-navy">
          <p>Tama PR is not about being the loudest in the room.</p>
          <p>It's about being honest.</p>
          <p>And using voice with intention.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Meet the Founder -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-warm-white">
    <div class="max-w-[1200px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-16">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[320px_1fr] gap-12 lg:gap-16 items-start">
        <!-- Photo -->
        <div class="flex flex-col items-center lg:items-start reveal">
          <img
            src={tamaPortrait.src}
            alt="Tama Munira Wazome"
            class="w-[220px] h-[220px] lg:w-[280px] lg:h-[280px] rounded-2xl object-cover object-top"
          />
          <div class="mt-5 text-center lg:text-left">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-[24px] text-navy">Tama Munira Wazome</h3>
            <p class="text-[14px] text-terracotta font-medium mt-1">Founder & Communications Lead</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Bio -->
        <div class="reveal reveal-delay-2">
          <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[2px] uppercase text-terracotta mb-5">Meet Tama</p>
          <div class="space-y-5 text-[16px] leading-[1.85] text-text-muted">
            <p>
              A communications strategist, advocate, and storyteller committed to ethical, purpose-driven public relations. With a deep understanding of cultural narratives, media dynamics, and human-centered communication, Tama has built a practice rooted in listening, integrity, and intentional advocacy.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- A Note From Tama -->
          <div class="mt-8 bg-cream rounded-xl p-6 md:p-8 border-l-3 border-amber">
            <h4 class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[1.5px] uppercase text-amber mb-3">A Note From Tama</h4>
            <div class="space-y-4 font-serif text-[17px] italic text-navy leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                This work is my response to a question I carried for years: What if communication could be different? Slower. More honest. Rooted in responsibility rather than reach.
              </p>
              <p>
                Every client I take on, every story I help shape, is an extension of that question. I don't have all the answers&mdash;but I show up with curiosity, care, and the belief that your voice matters.
              </p>
              <p>
                If that resonates with you, I'd love to listen.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Philosophy -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-cream">
    <div class="max-w-[1200px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-16">
      <div class="text-center mb-12 reveal">
        <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[2px] uppercase text-terracotta mb-5">Our Philosophy</p>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-[28px] md:text-[32px] text-navy">PR should be as real as the people it represents.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        {philosophy.map((item, i) => (
          <div class={`bg-warm-white border border-navy/[0.06] rounded-xl p-7 reveal reveal-delay-${i + 1}`}>
            <h3 class="font-serif text-[18px] text-navy mb-3">{item.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-[14px] leading-relaxed text-text-muted">{item.description}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Our Lenses / Five Pillars -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-navy">
    <div class="max-w-[1200px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-16">
      <div class="text-center mb-14 reveal">
        <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[2px] uppercase text-amber/50 mb-5">Our Lenses</p>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-[24px] md:text-[32px] text-white max-w-[600px] mx-auto">
          Tama PR stands on five pillars &mdash; the lenses through which we communicate, create, educate, and advocate.
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        {pillars.map((p, i) => (
          <div class={`flex items-start gap-6 p-6 bg-white/[0.03] border border-white/[0.06] rounded-lg reveal reveal-delay-${i + 1}`}>
            <span class="text-[13px] font-semibold text-amber/50 mt-0.5">{p.number}</span>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-[18px] text-white mb-1">{p.title}</h3>
              <p class="text-[14px] text-white/50 mb-0.5">{p.tagline}</p>
              <p class="text-[13px] text-white/30 italic">{p.subtitle}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-warm-white text-center">
    <div class="max-w-[600px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-16 reveal">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-[28px] md:text-[32px] text-navy mb-4">Ready to begin?</h2>
      <p class="text-[16px] text-text-muted mb-8">No pressure. No pitch. Just listening.</p>
      <MagneticButton href="/contact" variant="primary">Schedule a Discovery Call</MagneticButton>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
